    "body": "Tilde-d versions for dependencies is generally \"bad practice\" and meant that npm install wouldn't update to minecraft-protocol 0.10.1 if 0.10.0 was already installed.\r\nWas causing a few issues.",
    "closed_at": "2013-07-09T19:37:38Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "body": "I don't think this is necessary.\r\n\r\nTilde versions are not bad practice, in fact they are the default that npm uses. See https://npmjs.org/doc/json.html#Tilde-Version-Ranges\r\n\r\nTilde versions mean, \"use this stable version, but accept bug fixes\".\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n> wouldn't update to minecraft-protocol 0.10.1 if 0.10.0 was already installed.\r\n\r\nTry this: rm -rf node_modules/minecraft-protocol/ && npm install",
            "created_at": "2013-05-10T01:18:15Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/PrismarineJS/mineflayer/pull/152#issuecomment-17699436",
            "id": 17699436,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/PrismarineJS/mineflayer/issues/152",
            "updated_at": "2013-05-10T01:18:15Z",
